{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872478059,"sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3f8875001yog9aBMtfo1kw0","messageID":"msg_d7a3f7b16001mpJmaIhcpdu2kJ","sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1f275c743ac046ae9098a4c6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing RBAC configuration (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) in the agentcube manifests module.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-031\n10: - **Module**: `manifests`\n11: - **Language**: YAML\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: ServiceAccount Definitions\n17: \n18: ### AR-031-001: Agent ServiceAccount\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes namespace for agentcube components\n21: - **WHEN** creating ServiceAccount for agent pods\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n23: - **AND** SHALL be created in each target namespace\n24: - **AND** SHALL include appropriate imagePullSecrets if needed\n25: \n26: ### AR-031-002: Controller ServiceAccount\n27: \n28: - **GIVEN** namespace for agentcube control plane\n29: - **WHEN** creating ServiceAccount for controllers\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n31: - **AND** SHALL be created in the agentcube-system namespace\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Scenario: Role Definitions\n36: \n37: ### AR-031-003: Agent Runtime Role\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n40: - **WHEN** defining Role for agent ServiceAccount\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for AgentRuntime CRD (get, list, watch)\n42: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRD (get, list, watch, update, patch)\n43: - **AND** SHALL include permissions forPods (get, list, watch, create, delete)\n44: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Services (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n45: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent-runtime`\n46: \n47: ### AR-031-004: Agent Namespace Role\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n50: - **WHEN** defining Role for agent namespace access\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for ConfigMaps (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n52: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Secrets (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n53: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Events (get, list, watch, create)\n54: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n55: \n56: ### AR-031-005: Controller ClusterRole\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** cluster-wide scope\n59: - **WHEN** defining ClusterRole for controller\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for AgentRuntime CRD (all verbs)\n61: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRD (all verbs)\n62: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for namespaces (get, list, watch)\n63: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for pods (all verbs)\n64: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for services (all verbs)\n65: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for configmaps (all verbs)\n66: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for secrets (all verbs)\n67: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for events (all verbs)\n68: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Scenario: RoleBinding Definitions\n73: \n74: ### AR-031-006: Agent Runtime RoleBinding\n75: \n76: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n77: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for agent ServiceAccount\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-agent` SA to `agentcube-agent-runtime` Role\n79: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent-runtime`\n80: - **AND** SHALL reference correct namespace\n81: \n82: ### AR-031-007: Agent Namespace RoleBinding\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n85: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for agent namespace access\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-agent` SA to `agentcube-agent` Role\n87: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n88: - **AND** SHALL reference correct namespace\n89: \n90: ### AR-031-008: Controller RoleBinding\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** agentcube-system namespace\n93: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for controller\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-controller` SA to `agentcube-controller` ClusterRole\n95: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n96: - **AND** SHALL use ClusterRoleBinding for cluster-wide access\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Scenario: RBAC Deployment\n101: \n102: ### AR-031-009: RBAC YAML structure\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** manifests directory\n105: - **WHEN** organizing RBAC YAML files\n106: - **THEN** they SHALL be placed under `manifests/rbac/`\n107: - **AND** SHALL include ServiceAccount YAML files\n108: - **AND** SHALL include Role YAML files\n109: - **AND** SHALL include RoleBinding YAML files\n110: \n111: ### AR-031-010: Namespace isolation\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n114: - **WHEN** defining roles\n115: - **THEN** Agent roles SHALL be namespace-scoped (Role)\n116: - **AND** Controller roles SHALL be cluster-scoped (ClusterRole)\n117: - **AND** RoleBindings SHALL reference correct namespaces\n118: \n119: ### AR-031-011: Least privilege principle\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n122: - **WHEN** defining permissions\n123: - **THEN** Agent SA SHALL only have permissions needed for runtime\n124: - **AND** Controller SA SHALL have permissions needed for reconciliation\n125: - **AND** No wildcard (*) permissions SHALL be used unless absolutely necessary\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Scenario: Validation\n130: \n131: ### AR-031-012: YAML syntax validation\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** RBAC YAML files\n134: - **WHEN** running `kubectl apply --dry-run=client`\n135: - **THEN** all YAMLs SHALL be valid Kubernetes resources\n136: - **AND** SHALL pass schema validation\n137: \n138: ### AR-031-013: RBAC consistency\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n141: - **WHEN** applying to cluster\n142: - **THEN** ServiceAccounts SHALL exist before RoleBindings reference them\n143: - **AND** Roles SHALL exist before RoleBindings reference them\n144: - **AND** All referenced namespaces SHALL exist\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## References\n149: \n150: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation\n151: - agentcube design: `design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 151 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing RBAC configuration (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) in the agentcube manifests module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-031\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: ServiceAccount Definitions\n\n### AR-031-001: Agent ServiceAccount\n\n- **GIVEN** Kubernetes namespace for agentcube components","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872478046,"end":1775872478056}}}}
