{"type":"text","timestamp":1775872487199,"sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3fad28001BZUjNe5EBlBMcu","messageID":"msg_d7a3fa27c001k1cPo8iDuUCAbL","sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the proposal.md based on the delta-spec and following the AR-030 format:","time":{"start":1775872487197,"end":1775872487197}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872524773,"sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3faf20001tB5H46YW2jkZLI","messageID":"msg_d7a3fa27c001k1cPo8iDuUCAbL","sessionID":"ses_285c0e4f5ffelpq9u3QY0wGlKK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c62c2323201e4eeebca56aa7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement comprehensive RBAC configuration for AgentCube, defining ServiceAccounts, Roles, and RoleBindings to enable secure, least-privilege access control for agent pods and controllers across namespaces.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube requires proper RBAC configuration to secure communication between its components. The current Helm chart includes basic ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding, but lacks:\n- Namespace-scoped Roles for agents\n- Dedicated ServiceAccounts for agents and controllers\n- Granular permissions per component type\n\nThe delta-spec AR-031 defines specific acceptance scenarios that need implementation.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate RBAC manifests under `manifests/rbac/` that:\n- Define `agentcube-agent` ServiceAccount for agent pods\n- Define `agentcube-controller` ServiceAccount for control plane\n- Create namespace-scoped Roles with least-privilege permissions\n- Create ClusterRole for controller with full reconciliation access\n- Bind ServiceAccounts to appropriate Roles\n\n### Value\n\n- **Security**: Follows Kubernetes RBAC best practices with least-privilege\n- **Isolation**: Namespace-scoped agent roles vs cluster-scoped controller roles\n- **Maintainability**: Clear separation of concerns between agent and controller\n- **Compliance**: Meets enterprise security requirements for multi-tenant access\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Agent ServiceAccount | `manifests/rbac/agent-serviceaccount.yaml` | `agentcube-agent` SA with optional imagePullSecrets |\n| Controller ServiceAccount | `manifests/rbac/controller-serviceaccount.yaml` | `agentcube-controller` SA in agentcube-system |\n| Agent Runtime Role | `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-role.yaml` | Namespace Role for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs |\n| Agent Namespace Role | `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-role.yaml` | Namespace Role for ConfigMaps, Secrets, Events |\n| Controller ClusterRole | `manifests/rbac/controller-clusterrole.yaml` | ClusterRole for full CRD reconciliation |\n| Agent Runtime RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds agent SA to runtime Role |\n| Agent Namespace RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds agent SA to namespace Role |\n| Controller RoleBinding | `manifests/rbac/controller-rolebinding.yaml` | Binds controller SA to ClusterRole |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- RBAC for existing Helm chart templates (already exists)\n- Integration with external identity providers (OIDC, LDAP)\n- Pod security policies / Pod security standards\n- Network policies\n- Mutating/admission webhooks\n- Multi-cluster RBAC synchronization\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| Kubernetes 1.19+ | RBAC API versions | Required |\n| AgentRuntime CRD | CRD for agent runtime management | Required |\n| CodeInterpreter CRD | CRD for code interpreter management | Required |\n| agentcube-system namespace | Controller namespace | Required |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `design.md` — AgentCube architecture design\n- `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md` — Acceptance scenarios\n- `manifests/agentcube/templates/rbac/` — Existing RBAC templates (AR-030)\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Agent pods** — Use agentcube-agent SA for RBAC\n2. **Controller pods** — Use agentcube-controller SA\n3. **Helm chart** — May reference or include these RBAC manifests\n4. **Documentation** — Reference RBAC configuration for operators\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Permission too broad | High | Follow least-privilege; separate agent vs controller roles |\n| Missing CRD permissions | Medium | Verify CRD API groups match deployed resources |\n| Namespace mismatch | Medium | Document required namespaces; add validation |\n| Upgrade path | Low | Document migration from AR-030 RBAC |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Use only ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Simpler, single scope, easier to manage\n**Cons**: No namespace isolation, grants cluster-wide permissions to agents, violates least-privilege\n\n### Option 2: Extend existing Helm RBAC templates (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Reuses existing code, maintains single source of truth\n**Cons**: Mixes Helm templated RBAC with static manifests, unclear separation\n\n### Option 3: Separate RBAC manifests in manifests/rbac/ (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Clear separation, namespace-scoped agent roles, least-privilege, easy to audit\n**Cons**: Additional files to maintain, must sync with Helm chart\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### ServiceAccount Definitions\n\n#### agentcube-agent\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-agent\n  namespace: <target-namespace>\nimagePullSecrets: []  # Optional, from values\n```\n\n#### agentcube-controller\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-controller\n  namespace: agentcube-system\n```\n\n### Role Definitions\n\n#### agentcube-agent-runtime (Namespace-scoped)\n| API Group | Resources | Verbs |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh | agentruntimes | get, list, watch |\n| runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh | codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, update, patch |\n| \"\" | pods | get, list, watch, create, delete |\n| \"\" | services | get, list, watch, create, update, delete |\n\n#### agentcube-agent (Namespace-scoped)\n| API Group | Resources | Verbs |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| \"\" | configmaps | get, list, watch, create, update, delete |\n| \"\" | secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, delete |\n| \"\" | events | get, list, watch, create |\n\n#### agentcube-controller (Cluster-scoped)\n| API Group | Resources | Verbs |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh | agentruntimes | * |\n| runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh | codeinterpreters | * |\n| \"\" | namespaces | get, list, watch |\n| \"\" | pods | * |\n| \"\" | services | * |\n| \"\" | configmaps | * |\n| \"\" | secrets | * |\n| \"\" | events | * |\n\n### RoleBinding Structure\n\n- `agentcube-agent-runtime` RoleBinding → binds agent SA to agent-runtime Role\n- `agentcube-agent` RoleBinding → binds agent SA to agent namespace Role\n- `agentcube-controller` ClusterRoleBinding → binds controller SA to controller ClusterRole\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: ServiceAccounts\n\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/agent-serviceaccount.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/controller-serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n### Phase 2: Roles\n\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-role.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-role.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/controller-clusterrole.yaml`\n\n### Phase 3: RoleBindings\n\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/agent-runtime-rolebinding.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/agent-namespace-rolebinding.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/rbac/controller-rolebinding.yaml`\n\n### Phase 4: Validation\n\n- [ ] Run `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` on all manifests\n- [ ] Verify CRD API groups match actual deployed CRDs\n- [ ] Test namespace isolation\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| RBAC-001 | Agent ServiceAccount | ServiceAccount named `agentcube-agent` exists |\n| RBAC-002 | Controller ServiceAccount | ServiceAccount named `agentcube-controller` exists in agentcube-system |\n| RBAC-003 | Agent Runtime Role | Role grants CRD + pod + service permissions |\n| RBAC-004 | Agent Namespace Role | Role grants configmap + secret + event permissions |\n| RBAC-005 | Controller ClusterRole | ClusterRole grants full CRUD on CRDs + cluster resources |\n| RBAC-006 | Agent Runtime RoleBinding | Binds agent SA to agent-runtime Role |\n| RBAC-007 | Agent Namespace RoleBinding | Binds agent SA to agent namespace Role |\n| RBAC-008 | Controller RoleBinding | Binds controller SA to controller ClusterRole |\n| RBAC-009 | YAML syntax | All YAMLs pass `kubectl apply --dry-run=client` |\n| RBAC-010 | Least privilege | No wildcard (*) permissions in agent Roles |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| ServiceAccounts | 1 hour |\n| Roles | 2 hours |\n| RoleBindings | 1 hour |\n| Validation | 1 hour |\n| **Total** | **5 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other ARs\n\nAR-031 provides RBAC foundation for:\n\n- AR-030 — Extends existing Helm chart RBAC with detailed manifests\n- AgentRuntime controller — Requires controller ClusterRole\n- CodeInterpreter controller — Requires controller ClusterRole\n- Agent pods — Will use agentcube-agent ServiceAccount","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/manifests/agentcube/templates/clusterrole.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [4:2] Unexpected flow-map-start at node end\nERROR [4:3] Unexpected seq-item-ind at node end\nERROR [4:5] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [4:28] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [4:29] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [5:1] Unexpected